<doc>
  <member name="TRUECOLORINFO">
    <summary>
      <para>The <b>TRUECOLORINFO</b> structure contains color palette and bitmask information for a video image.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This structure is not used for some RGB formats. For more information about which fields are valid under different circumstances, see the Platform SDK documentation for <b>BITMAPINFO</b>.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/directshow-structures">DirectShow Structures</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/windows/desktop/api/amvideo/ns-amvideo-videoinfo">VIDEOINFO</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="TRUECOLORINFO.dwBitMasks">
    <summary>
      <para>Array of color masks (one per color element).</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="TRUECOLORINFO.bmiColors">
    <summary>
      <para>Array of palette colors.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>